The paper deals with generating high-quality person images with arbitrary poses, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The proposed model uses multi-scale generators and discriminators, which involves handling different levels of visual features, making it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of conditional generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image generation is a popular research area in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
